MobileViT (2021) - The Simpler Hybrid
MobileViT is a hybrid model that uses CNNs to capture local details (textures, edges) and Transformers to capture global context (overall shape and relationships) .

How It Works (Simple Version)
Image → CNN (learns local features) → Transformer (learns global relationships) → CNN → Result

The Key Insight
Instead of applying Transformer to the whole image (which is expensive), MobileViT:
Unfolds the image into small patches
Applies Transformer only to those patches to understand patch-to-patch relationships
Folds them back into a full image 

Why It's Good for Your Waste Project
Benefit			Explanation
Smaller			5.3-5.6 million parameters (vs ResNet50's 25.6M) 
Fast			~18ms per image on mobile hardware 
Accurate		85%+ accuracy on image classification 
Easy to explain	"CNN for details, Transformer for the big picture"


Simple Architecture Diagram:

Input Image
    ↓
[Convolution Blocks] → Learns textures, edges, local patterns
    ↓
[MobileViT Block] → Learns how patches relate to each other
    ↓
[Convolution Blocks] → Fuses local + global features
    ↓
Classification Output
